          h2 Quill automates the process of grading homework assignments.
          p Quill presents students with articles that have grammatical errors embedded into them.  For example, a 300 word article on Ernest Shackelton has 30 grammatical errors embedded into it. Students play a game in which they have to find and correct all of the errors.
          p Students are then told which errors they did not  catch, and students are given a personalized homework assignment in which they practice writing out the grammatical rules they did not understand.
          p Teachers sign up an entire class, assign articles to the class, and monitor their students' progress. Students proofread a series of articles. Each article introduces progressively harder concepts. We cover all of the grammatical concepts from the Common Core State Standards for grades 1-8.
